# Spec-Driven Development (Spec Kit)

This project uses **GitHub Spec Kit** (`.specify/`). Follow spec-driven development for all non-trivial work.

## Workflow Order

1. `/speckit.constitution` — project principles (when starting or changing standards)
2. `/speckit.specify` — feature specification before coding
3. `/speckit.clarify` — resolve ambiguity (optional, before plan)
4. `/speckit.plan` — implementation plan from spec
5. `/speckit.tasks` — actionable task breakdown
6. `/speckit.implement` — execute against spec and tasks

## Rules

- Do not implement features without a spec or approved plan in `.specify/`.
- Keep specs, plans, and tasks in `.specify/` aligned with code changes.
- Update agent context via `/speckit.agent-context.update` when architecture shifts.
- Reference `.specify/memory/constitution.md` for project principles.
- Bug fixes under 5 lines may skip spec; everything else needs `/speckit.specify` or an existing spec.

## Before Merging

- Spec and implementation must match.
- Run `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`, and `pnpm snyk:test`.
